    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n**1. Use this chatbot to get debugging help.**\r\n- If you are stuck on Levels 2 or 3, use this chatbot can help you understand error messages, debug logic issues, and suggest next steps.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**2. Some ways to ask the chatbot for help:**\r\n- **Understanding Error Messages:** *\"I got this error: NameError: name 'painter' is not defined. What does it mean?\"*\r\n- **Debugging Unexpected Behavior:** *\"My code runs, but it doesn't do what I expect. It should paint a line but it doesn't. What could be wrong?\"*\r\n- **Finding the Best Debugging Strategy:** *\"What debugging steps should I try if my program isn't working correctly?\"*\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**3. Use the chatbot's suggestions to debug your code.**\r\n- If the chatbot suggests checking values, use `print` statements in your program.\r\n- If the chatbot points to an error message, find the most important lines and identify what went wrong.\r\n- If the chatbot suggests a fix, try modifying your code and re-running your tests.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**4. Return to the level and test your fixes.**\r\n- After getting help, go back to your programming level (Level 2 or 3) and apply what you learned.\r\n- Re-run the tests to check if the problem is fixed.\r\n\r\n::: details [**Tips for Using the Chatbot Effectively**]\r\n- Be specific—describe exactly what’s happening in your program.\r\n- Copy and paste error messages to help the chatbot analyze them.\r\n- Ask follow-up questions if the chatbot’s response isn’t clear.\r\n- Test one change at a time and rerun the program after each fix.\r\n:::",
